{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "Capacitor Memory Effect Demo",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Capacitor Memory Effect Demo",
    "description": "Use the slide switch like a “store / recall” control. Flip west (charge): USB → 470Ω → 1000µF → ground — the cap stores energy (longer charge = more stored). Flip east (recall): the cap powers the red LED through the east branch while USB is off that path — the LED fades as the “memory” empties. Try a short charge vs a long charge and compare fade time. Cap on column 5 (+ toward north); charge resistor west; LED east at 90°."
  },
